{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"FileLock","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This type is intended to coordinate ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"multiple processes"}]},{"text":" that all agree to use the same","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"lock-file path. The underlying lock is managed by the operating system and is:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Exclusive (write) lock"}]},{"type":"text","text":": only one process at a time may hold it."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Shared (read) lock"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": multiple processes may hold it concurrently, as long as no"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"exclusive lock is held on the same file."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"heading","text":"Important semantics","anchor":"Important-semantics","level":3},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Locks are ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"per process","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":", not per thread. From the OSâ€™s point of view, a process","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"either holds a lock on the file or it does not; individual threads are not tracked.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This means "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FileLock"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"not a replacement for a mutex between threads"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"same process. If two threads both call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lockExclusive()"},{"type":"text","text":" (directly or via separate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FileLock"},{"type":"text","text":" instances), the OS will happily report success to both, because the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"process","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" already owns the lock."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FileLock"},{"type":"text","text":" itself is "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"not thread-safe"}]},{"type":"text","text":": if you share a single instance between"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"threads, you must protect calls to its methods with your own in-process synchronization"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(e.g. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSLock"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DispatchQueue"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this type when you need:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Mutual exclusion between ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"processes"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" (e.g. only one instance of a job\/tool running),","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Or to guard access to a shared on-disk resource across multiple executables or daemons."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"thread-level","type":"text"}]},{"text":" synchronization ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"within a single process","type":"text"}]},{"text":", prefer standard","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"primitives such as ","type":"text"},{"code":"DispatchQueue","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"NSLock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", or ","type":"text"},{"code":"pthread_mutex_t","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", and optionally","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"combine them with ","type":"text"},{"code":"FileLock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if you also need cross-process safety.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"Example (exclusive, non-blocking)","anchor":"Example-exclusive-non-blocking","level":3},{"type":"codeListing","code":["","do {","  let lock = try FileLock(path: \"\/tmp\/myapp.job.lock\")","  try lock.lockExclusive()","  \/\/ This process \"won\" the lock; safe to run the job here.","  runJob()","} catch {","      \/\/ another process is already running the job","}"],"syntax":"swift"}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A small wrapper around POSIX "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"flock()"},{"type":"text","text":" for "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"cross-process"}]},{"type":"text","text":" file locking."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/FlockKit\/documentation\/FlockKit"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/FlockKit\/documentation\/FlockKit\/FileLock"},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"FileLock","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Class","title":"FileLock","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"FileLock","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"FlockKit"}],"symbolKind":"class","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:8FlockKit8FileLockC"},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/FlockKit\/documentation\/FlockKit\/FileLock\/init(path:)"],"generated":true,"title":"Initializers","anchor":"Initializers"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/FlockKit\/documenta